				\begin{document}$$ \boldsymbol{y}\in {\mathcal{R}}^n $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M2" display="inline"><mml:mi mathvariant="bold-italic">y</mml:mi><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi mathvariant="script">R</mml:mi><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13073_2021_908_Article_IEq1.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> be a gene expression vector modeling its expression values across <italic>n</italic> samples (e.g., <italic>n</italic> cells from single-cell data) and <inline-formula id="IEq2"><alternatives><tex-math id="M3">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
